.TH "irq_create_mapping_affinity" 9 "irq_create_mapping_affinity" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
irq_create_mapping_affinity \- Map a hardware interrupt into linux irq space
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" irq_create_mapping_affinity
.BI "(struct irq_domain *domain "  ","
.BI "irq_hw_number_t hwirq "  ","
.BI "const struct irq_affinity_desc *affinity "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "domain" 12
domain owning this hardware interrupt or NULL for default domain
.IP "hwirq" 12
hardware irq number in that domain space
.IP "affinity" 12
irq affinity
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Only one mapping per hardware interrupt is permitted. Returns a linux
irq number.
If the sense/trigger is to be specified, \fBset_irq_type\fP should be called
on the number returned from that call.
